#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:7
msgid ""
"Conversations in Mattermost are crucial to company productivity and "
"success. Keeping conversations organized in the sidebar creates an "
"efficient workplace. Using a web browser or the desktop app, you can "
"customize your own channel sidebar based on how you prefer to use "
"Mattermost. Customizations you make are only visible to you, are visible "
"when using the mobile app, and won't affect what your teammates see in "
"their sidebars."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:9
msgid "Here's how your sidebar is set up by default:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:11
msgid ""
"All public and private channels you've joined are listed in the "
"**Channels** category, sorted alphabetically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:12
msgid ""
"All your direct messages and group messages are listed in the **Direct "
"Messages** category, sorted by recent activity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:15
msgid "What can you customize?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:17
msgid ""
"Using Mattermost in a web browser or the desktop app, you can customize "
"your sidebar in the following ways:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:19
msgid "`Create custom categories <#create-custom-categories>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:20
msgid ""
"`Group and order channels into your categories <#organize-channels-in-"
"categories>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:21
msgid "`Mute and unmute entire categories <#mute-and-unmute-categories>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:22
msgid "`Mark entire categories as read <#mark-channel-categories-as-read>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:23
msgid ""
"`Sort channels in each category <#sort-channels-in-categories>`__ "
"manually, alphabetically, or by recent activity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:24
msgid ""
"`Filter your sidebar to view unread channels only <#group-unread-"
"channels-separately>`__, or choose to group unread messages into an "
"**Unreads** category"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:25
msgid ""
"`Manage your direct messages <#manage-direct-messages>`__ by sorting them"
" alphabetically or by recent activity, and by setting how many to display"
" in your sidebar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:26
msgid ""
"`Make channel categories work for you <#make-categories-work-for-you>`__ "
"by prefixing category names with emojis, by collapsing and expanding "
"categories, by reordering categories, and by adding direct message "
"conversations to categories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:-1
msgid "Organize your channel sidebar with channel categories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:32
msgid "Create custom categories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:34
msgid ""
"Create custom categories to group channels together for quicker and "
"easier navigation. For example, you can create a category called "
"\"Design\" or \"Marketing\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:36
msgid ""
"To create categories, select the **+** symbol at the top of the sidebar. "
"Or, select the **More options** |more-icon| icon in the sidebar on any "
"category header, then select **Create New Category**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../<rst_prolog>:16
msgid "Use the More icon to access additional message options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:38
msgid ""
"Next, type a category name, select **Create**, then drag any channels or "
"direct messages into this new category. You can also multi-select "
"channels and direct messages to drag them together as a group by pressing"
" :kbd:`Ctrl` or :kbd:`Shift` and selecting on Windows or Linux, or "
":kbd:`⌘` or :kbd:`⇧` and selecting on Mac. See the section `drag and drop"
" selections <#drag-and-drop-selections>`__ below for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:40
msgid "Your custom categories can't be shared with other Mattermost users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:43
msgid "Rename categories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:45
msgid ""
"Select the **Category options** icon in the sidebar, then select **Rename"
" Category**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:46
msgid "Type a new category name, then select **Rename**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:49
msgid "Delete categories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:51
msgid ""
"Select the **Category options** icon in the sidebar, then select **Delete"
" Category**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:52
msgid "Select **Delete** to confirm or select **X** to cancel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:54
msgid ""
"All channels and direct message conversations in the deleted category "
"move back to their default **Channels** and **Direct Messages** "
"categories. Deleting a category never removes you from channels you have "
"joined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:57
msgid "Organize channels in categories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:59
msgid ""
"Once you've created categories, you can move channels around to organize "
"your sidebar by dragging and dropping, or by moving."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:62
msgid "Drag and drop selections"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:64
msgid "To select multiple channels:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:66
msgid ""
"Select sequential channels and/or direct messages by pressing "
":kbd:`Shift` while selecting on Windows or Linux, or :kbd:`⇧` while "
"selecting  on Mac."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:67
msgid ""
"Select non-sequential channels and/or direct messages by pressing "
":kbd:`Ctrl` while selecting on Windows or Linux, or :kbd:`⌘` while "
"selecting on Mac"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:68
msgid "Press :kbd:`ESC` to clear channel or direct message selections."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:70
msgid ""
"Using the Mattermost web or desktop app, drag selected channels and/or "
"direct messages between or within categories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:74
msgid ""
"Multi-selected channels and direct messages move together as a group in "
"the order they originally appeared."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Move a group of selected channels by dragging them to a new location in "
"the channel sidebar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:80
msgid "Move selections"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:82
msgid ""
"In addition to selecting and dragging, you can specify a category "
"destination for selected channels and/or direct messages. To do this, "
"select the **Channel options** icon in the sidebar and then select **Move"
" to**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:-1
msgid "Move a group of selected channels to a specified category destination."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:87
msgid ""
"You can also specify a category destination for the current channel or "
"conversation using the **Move to** option directly from the channel "
"header. Channels that have been moved to a category will display a "
"checkmark next to the category name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:-1
msgid "Move channels or conversations directly from the channel header."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:93
msgid "Mute and unmute categories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:95
msgid ""
"When you mute or unmute a category, all channels within that category are"
" also muted or unmuted. You can selectively unmute specific channels "
"within a muted category."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:97
msgid ""
"Select the **Category options** icon in the sidebar, then select **Mute "
"Category**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:99
msgid "Once a category is muted:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:101
msgid ""
"Email, desktop, and push notifications are disabled for all channels in "
"the category."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:102
msgid "A mute icon displays next to each channel name in the category."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:103
msgid ""
"The category and all of its channels appear at reduced opacity in the "
"left-hand sidebar. Channels in the category aren't marked as unread "
"unless you’re mentioned directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:105
msgid ""
"To unmute the category, select the **Category options** icon in the "
"sidebar, then select **Unmute Category**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Mute or unmute a category to mute or unmute all channels within that "
"category. You can also selectively unmute specific channels within a "
"muted category."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:111
msgid "Mark channel categories as read"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:113
msgid ""
"When you mark a channel category as read, all channels within that "
"category are marked as read. You can selectively mark specific channels "
"as unread where preferred."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:115
msgid ""
"Select the **Category options** icon in the sidebar, then select **Mark "
"category as read**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:118
msgid "Sort channels in categories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:120
msgid ""
"Select the **Category options** icon in the sidebar, then select **Sort**"
" and choose from **Alphabetically**, **Recent Activity**, or "
"**Manually**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Sort channels within a category alphabetically, by recent activity, or "
"manually."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:126
msgid "Group unread channels separately"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:128
msgid ""
"By default, Mattermost provides a one-click **Unreads** filter to only "
"show channels with unread activity. Alternatively, you may choose to "
"automatically group unread channels in their own category at the top of "
"your sidebar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:130
msgid ""
"Go to **Settings > Sidebar**, set **Group unread channels separately** to"
" **On**, then select **Save**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:132
msgid ""
"When this setting is enabled, all unread messages appear only in the "
"**Unreads** category, sorted with mentions first."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:133
msgid ""
"When this setting is disabled, all unread messages appear within their "
"respective categories and channels. You can use the **Unread filter** to "
"focus on only unread channels in the sidebar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:135
msgid ""
"When enabled, unread channels with mentions will sort to the top of the "
"category."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:-1
msgid ""
"The Unreads filter only shows channels with unread activity. You can also"
" group unread channels into their own category at the top of the channel "
"sidebar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:142
msgid ""
"If you prefer to see only unread channels in their respective categories,"
" we recommend collapsing your custom categories and disabling **Group "
"unread channels separately** under **Settings > Sidebar**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:145
msgid "Manage direct messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:147
msgid ""
"To sort your direct messages, select the **Channel options** icon in the "
"sidebar, then select **Sort** and choose from **Alphabetically** or "
"**Recent Activity**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:150
msgid "How many direct messages to display?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:152
msgid ""
"Control how many direct message conversations display in the **Direct "
"Messages** category to keep your conversations manageable. You can choose"
" to show all messages or a fixed number of messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:154
msgid ""
"To configure the number of direct messages to display, go to **Settings >"
" Sidebar**, then set **Number of direct messages to show**. Or select the"
" **Channel options** icon in the sidebar, then select **Show**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:156
msgid ""
"Choose to show **10**, **15**, **20**, or **40** messages. Once you "
"exceed the number of direct messages configured, older messages are "
"hidden from the **Direct Messages** category. You can always increase the"
" number of conversations displayed to see older direct messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:-1
msgid ""
"alt: Control the number of direct message conversations to display under "
"the Direct Messages category by showing all messages or a fixed number of"
" messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:162
msgid ""
"Direct message conversations that you add to custom categories don't "
"count against the maximum number of conversations shown in the **Direct "
"Messages** category."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:165
msgid "Make categories work for you"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:168
msgid "Prefix channel category names with emojis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:170
msgid ""
"Channel category names can include emojis. Specify the emoji by its name "
"in the format ``:smile:``. We recommend prefixing channel category names "
"with emojis for the following reasons:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:172
msgid ""
"Emojis can make it easier for users to quickly identify and manage "
"channels and channel categories, particularly in large workspaces with "
"many channels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:173
msgid ""
"Sharing the same emoji across channels and categories related to a "
"specific category or function helps maintain organization and consistency"
" across the workspace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:174
msgid ""
"Making channel categories more visually distinct with emojis helps users "
"find what they need more quickly and easily at a glance, reducing the "
"time spent searching for the right place to take action."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:175
msgid ""
"New users can quickly understand the purpose of various channels and "
"channel categories based on their emoji prefixes without needing "
"extensive explanations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:176
msgid ""
"As users grasp channel structure through emojis, the time and effort "
"needed to train new members on navigating the workspace is reduced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:177
msgid ""
"A well-organized and visually appealing workspace can encourage users to "
"participate more actively, which can lead to more effective communication"
" and collaboration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:180
msgid "Categories are collapsible"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:182
msgid ""
"When you collapse a channel category, only unread channels display to "
"reduce unnecessary scrolling. When you expand a channel category, all "
"channels in the category display, including channels with unread "
"messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:185
msgid "Reorder categories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:187
msgid "Drag to reorder entire categories to prioritize important conversations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:190
msgid "Categories can contain direct message conversations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/preferences/customize-your-channel-sidebar.rst:192
msgid ""
"Select and drag direct messages into any category. You can also multi-"
"select direct messages to drag them together as a group."
msgstr ""

